Our Easter Bank Holiday kicked off with my well-being hour spent down Pets At Home looking for grot spray and then a wander down Oak Beck. Laugh a minute with Mr Vestibular who wanted to sample the blades of grass growing on riverbank 😱
Friday we went to an agility competition where the two weirdo black dogs marauded around and Stanley aired his grotty armpit.
Saturday I gutted and tinkered with the dog mobile v2
Sunday was the usual plus a late review of the mahoosive tear we put in the second hand caravan awning. 
Monday drove to Wolverhampton to buy a new awning. Realised most of our poles must be missing from the first awning because this smaller one weighs a tonne!! 
Stopped in Stafford on the way home for a tramp around the marshes and a visit to Stanley’s Original Mum.
All in all a delightful weekend

Another B.T.S post of the maneater palette that I want to share with you all is the making of the shade camouflage.

This shade performed so badly I originally didn't put it in. If you swipe across to the second slide, you can see the bright green matte I was going to use instead, purely because it actually performs, next to camouflage which barely showed up on my skin.

But I really loved the colour of the camouflage shade and it was something I really wanted to include in the palette. You can wear it as a monochromatic matte on your lid with a nice pair of lashes and it's just perfect and so easy for every day wear... I really, really wanted to put it in there!! 😂

So we went back and reformulated it. The first slide shows the old camouflage which you can see looks quite patchy, compared to the new - which picks up beautifully. It's still not as great as some of the other mattes in the palette, its such a difficult shade to formulate tbh! But it's a million times better than it was. I mean it barely even showed on my skin tone originally tbh!! Swipe to the second slide you can barely even see it 😂

I think we made so much progress with this shade, and I'm so glad it stayed in the palette. If you swipe across to the 3rd page you'll see that this shade was never in the original palette design.

But it is now one of my fave shades. Are you glad it made it in there? Or would you have preferred the bright green matte? Do you want to see that matte in the next palette?

Let me know 😋❤️

Microblading is a semi-permanent cosmetic tattooing technique that is used to create natural-looking eyebrows. It involves using a small hand-held tool with several tiny needles to create small, hair-like strokes in the eyebrow area, depositing pigment into the skin.

After the procedure, it is common to experience redness and slight swelling around the eyebrow area, and the pigment may appear darker than expected initially. This is because the pigment will fade over time as the skin heals and regenerates.

What is dermaplaning? 

It's a physical form of exfoliation in which I manually remove all dead skin + vellus hair that causes build up + congestion in your pores.

Dermaplaning will leave you with fresh, glowing, + immediate difference in how your skin looks + feels!

It will also allow your at home care to penetrate deeper + more effectively.
